oh my gosh...haha.  I just saw something pretty darn funny.

So my mom and I go to oscos to get meds, and this car pulls up next to this other car.  The guy gets out and starts to talk to the guy in the car.  Me and my nosy self looked and low and behold it was MATT DAVIS in the car! (if any of you know anything about me and my obsession-no-stalkession with Brent Holder, you will know that this is his Best Friend...) SO!  

The first guy (I'll call him Bruno [no, I don't know why])is looking kinda awkward and scared b/c my mom gets out of the car.  He looks at her then Matt.  Matt then hands Bruno money once my mom goes inside.  At fist I thought he was buying drugs.  Then, Bruno goes inside too.

I and my nosy nosy self is like, staring at Matt, to see what he's doing and I notice a lighter.  AH HA! Cigarettes!  but wait-he's already 18, so he wouldn't need anyone to buy them for him. But then I realize- DUH EILER!! THE DUDES GETTING ALCHOHOL! And low and behold, 5 minutes later, Bruno comes out w/ A pack of bud light and a brown bag and hands them to Mr. Davis and his prideful self knowing that he just got away with buying alchohol.  that scum bag.

So, that was interesting. He's pretty low to do that...haha. He didn't go to college so he stayed home getting drunk, thats sad.  Poor soul...

anywayz, just had to say that

peace and love

Heck yesshhh!!  Spring break honey child!

Wow, my day was extremely eventful!  

So it started out with me finding that I didn't make the play, which is totally a-ok with me b/c I'm a freshie and I still have 3 years left!! So I'm gonna work on tech with Kyle (maybe, if he sucks up and deals with the fact that he can't be the sound guy all the time...lol. jk)!  That'll be fun!

So the day continued and nothing happened.  UNTIL I get to Spanish.  We're watching this weird movie about this spanish girl turning 15 and her family is poor and she wants to be with this ugly as heck guy who has a FOR REAL MULLET!! hahahaha.  ANYWAYZ...we were watching, and then all the sudden, I get this pass.  It's to the nurse's office, and it said "come now" and it was highlighted.  Obviously, somehting was wrong.  The girl delivering the pass said I needed to take my stuff. 

I get my stuff and after hearing all these statements such as "OOWEEE!  They found the drugs in your locker!" and crap like that.

So I go to the office, and on my way I go through the possibilities.  I need to take advil...my throat hurts...Elijah's dead...Cecelie got shot (yea, I know, stupid, ryt?  Well the thing was highlighted!!). 

So I get there and my dads standing there and he tells me that mom had a really bad fall 6th hour and hit her head hard.  They had just taken her by ambulance in the hospital.

Obviously I thought death, lol.  Which wasn't the case at all. When I got there I could hear her laughing and joking around, so all was good.  

I guess this stool thing wasn't sturdy and she sat on it and hit her head on the wall or something. 

But she's all good now.  Her head's bleeding a bit, but all is good.

aight, thats all!!

Peace and Love

man, life is hectic. ok, I'm not complaining at all, because I'm so blessed to be able to be in a lot of things, but man, it is so tiring. I'm just a freshman, and already there's been the musical, speech, art 2 art, and many other things. PLEASE DON'T GET ME WRONG...I am sooo blessed to be in everything and meet so many awesome people and also blessed because as of now, there hasn't been a physical or emotional break-down. But, man, it kinda bothers me when people who don't do anything complain about being tired all the time. I'm not better than anyone, and I realize it's my choice to be in all these things, but man, I'm stupid for doing it, lol. So, sectionals are on Saturday. That'll rock! The main thing I need to remember is to be confident and know that whatever happens, life goes on and I have 3 more years, lol. I'm pretty nervous, but I think I'll do well, but let's hope hope hope I do well enough to go to state, man, that would be off the shizzle (whatever in the world that means, lol)!!!!! today was fun...I gue-OH YEA...I just remembered that I have to make up two tests...crap!! lol ANYWAYZ...it was kinda boring tho. Lunch was stupid, not as usual. The people at my table rock and are so diverse that it's so much fun to be at lunch, but, it's lunch. thats all it is. lol. At the same time tho...I can't help but get excited to go to lunch in the middle of everding's notes. My mind wonders to other things...because...lunch is just so much fun and cool, and. Yea, I know. I'm a freak, I go on and on about lunch, it's ok tho. lol I heard that John Heder died in a car accident, I don't think it's true because a lot of people would be talking about it, so I don't think so. But if it is true, blow me down and paint me red, that would suck. Art 2 art was fun. The cast is hilarious. Man, Nick and Adam are just so various and funny that it rocks. Me and Lindsey just kinda sit there and smile, because they're so smart, that's all we can agree to. lol. But then Adam'll get on one of his "phsycological" lectures...those are very fun. Because I actually pay attention to learn something. Don't think I don't understand what he says, because I can tell you that I fully understand everything that man says, it's just believing him that I'm not so sure about. lol ok, well, gotta go to bed. Peace and Love Leslie*

WELL, turns out I make finals and get 3rd overall, which means I'm going to SECTIONALS!!
